fields.Title: PLAZA / RIVER CRATER
fields.Description: You ask René about crater and get the streamlined history lesson without any messy checks or hubs within hubs withing hubs. Sweet and short.

fields.Title: START
input
Suggestion: "He finds your lack of historic know..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He finds your lack of historic knowledge troubling. A sign of mental deterioration in the proceeding generations.

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""I do," he nods, straightening his..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I do," he nods, straightening his back. "Fire from heavy artillery."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Commies, communists, socialists, a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Commies, communists, socialists, anarchists -- call them what you like. They just chose the name to feel special." The carabineer frowns. "Senseless sentimentality."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""This is communard propaganda! Guil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is communard propaganda! Guillaume would never do something like that. He is *LE LION*."

fields.Title: You: "(Look around) "I understand. I'd bo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: (Look around) "I understand. I'd bomb this place too."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""This place is the damn Beachhead,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This place is the damn Beachhead, son," he says, pointing to the bay. "They didn't do it because they didn't *like* it. They had to soften the commies up first."

fields.Title: Drama: "Some manner of self-deceit is prese..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Some manner of self-deceit is present in his thinking. Sounds like this Guillaume abandoned him and he doesn't want to admit it.

fields.Title: Hand/Eye Coordination: "An extremely inadvisable strategy a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: An extremely inadvisable strategy against automatic weapons. Be sure not to make the same mistake.

fields.Title: You: ""Was there an earthquake here?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Was there an earthquake here?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""The rest of the city got cleaned u..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The rest of the city got cleaned up, but Martinaise they keep as a *monument*." A dark shadow runs across his face. "And now the Union socialists are practically running the place."

fields.Title: Untitled hub (02)
You: ""Did *you* use artillery fire again..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Did *you* use artillery fire against them?"

fields.Title: You: ""Who was this Frissel?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who was this Frissel?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""A true King in both blood and mind..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "A true King in both blood and mind. Led Revachol before Frissel. He would have been better, but the damn commies drove him into exile."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Wait, Joyce said Guillaume ran and..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Wait, Joyce said Guillaume ran and his nephew, Frissel, was shot in his place.

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""This place is the damn Beachhead,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This place is the damn Beachhead, son," he says, pointing to the bay. "They had to soften the commies up first."

fields.Title: You: ""You mentioned Guillaume?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mentioned Guillaume?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""It's no use talking to you. You we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It's no use talking to you. You were still in daddy's balls when it happened. When *we* took our last stand against the filth and rode the cavalry straight into gunfire."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Fine," the carabineer replies shar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fine," the carabineer replies sharply. "What do you want now then?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""No," he replies, gaze wondering ov..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No," he replies, gaze wondering over the bay. "It was left by heavy artillery fire."

fields.Title: You: ""Why shell them here in Martinaise?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why shell them here in Martinaise?"

fields.Title: You: ""Actually I already know all this...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Actually I already know all this. I just wanted to know if you do too."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""No," he says without even smiling...."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No," he says without even smiling. "It was left by heavy artillery fire."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Mhmh," he grunts. "Don't get me wr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Mhmh," he grunts. "Don't get me wrong, officer. I hate those foreign dogs. But the enemy of my enemy and all that. They're the lesser evil."

fields.Title: You: ""Commies just don't understand how..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Commies just don't understand how money works."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Because that's what happens when c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Because that's what happens when communards hijack your country, execute your supreme leadership, and turn your capital into a slaughterhouse. You use *heavy ordnance* to clean up your home."

fields.Title: Endurance: "Something moves in your gut. It's a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something moves in your gut. It's almost like a tug.

You: ""Hold on -- the Coalition?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hold on -- the Coalition?"

fields.Title: You: ""This Coalition seems quite capable..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This Coalition seems quite capable, actually."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""I *would* have preferred if the ri..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I *would* have preferred if the right honourable King Guillaume returned to Revachol or even if that damn clown, Frissel, had risen from the grave and led us. Sadly that was not the case."

You: ""Okay, it's a crater left by artill..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Okay, it's a crater left by artillery fire -- but why?"

fields.Title: You: ""The Beachhead?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "The Beachhead?"

fields.Title: Gaston Martin: ""Blood ground..." The other one sha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Blood ground..." The other one shakes his head. "You got old René going there. Like he isn't angry enough already..."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""This is just what the commies want..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is just what the commies wanted. This was their plan all along. *This* is what they wanted to replace the rule of the Suzerain with."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""No, they don't. But I'm sorry it h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "No, they don't. But I'm sorry it had to be the Coalition. After eight years of fighting rabid commies, boiling cats for food and drinking piss in the mountains..." He takes a deep breath.

fields.Title: You: ""Nothing. I *don't* think. I just *..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Nothing. I *don't* think. I just *do*."

fields.Title: Composure: "He slouches as he says that. It mak..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He slouches as he says that. It makes him smaller, admitting they left the king to the mob.

fields.Title: Logic: "It was probably a bit more complica..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It was probably a bit more complicated than that.

fields.Title: You: ""Hmm... what exactly is a *suzerain..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm... what exactly is a *suzerain*?" (Conclude.)

René Arnoux: ""Sadly, no. It was the foreigners w..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Sadly, no. It was the foreigners who brought them to their knees. We fought valiantly -- too valiantly. So valiantly we got licked," he adds, squeezing a *boule* in his fist.

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Should've fought dirty. Like they..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Should've fought dirty. Like they did with their suicide sex cult propaganda and *mad anarchist women* strapped to shrapnel bombs. We didn't though. And we lacked *calibre*. God bless him, but the suzerain's cannons simply weren't big enough.“

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Damn Frissel -- he was the king we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn Frissel -- he was the king we couldn't protect. The carabineers failed him... and the crown." The old veteran falls silent and massages his chest. "He died in the hands of the *hoi polloi* in a very public execution."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""What else?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "What else?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""I'm sorry it had to be them." He l..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm sorry it had to be them." He looks down at his boots. "After eight years of fighting those hyenas, boiling cats for food and drinking piss in the mountains..."

fields.Title: You: ""They should have chosen a place aw..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "They should have chosen a place away from people and buildings."

fields.Title: You: ""Death Blow... sounds grim.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Death Blow... sounds grim."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""I'm just so damn sorry it had to b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm just so damn sorry it had to be the Coalition..." He isn't really paying attention to your words anymore. "After eight years of fighting those hyenas, boiling cats for food and drinking piss in the mountains..."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Why what?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why what?"

fields.Title: Jump to: [RENE MAIN HUB]
Volition: "There is not a shadow of a doubt in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is not a shadow of a doubt in his mind that this is the truth.

fields.Title: You: "Shake your head and look down at th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shake your head and look down at the crater.

fields.Title: You: ""How does Filippe the Third factor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "How does Filippe the Third factor into this?" (Point towards the monument.)

fields.Title: Empathy: "Soon they will forget everything. H..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Soon they will forget everything. Him too... Then he chooses anger over melancholy.

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Yes..." The man nods. "The terrain..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes..." The man nods. "The terrain here provides an interesting variety to a familiar game."

fields.Title: You: ""Ah, that explains all the war dama..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Ah, that explains all the war damage."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""He doesn't," the veteran replies s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "He doesn't," the veteran replies sharply. "That was one hundred years ago. Ain't got nothing to do with anything."

fields.Title: Gaston Martin: ""Well, it's your own damn fault," t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, it's your own damn fault," the jolly man remarks. "You, we, the Coalition, Revachol -- whoever you wanna blame -- never finished the job. Officially the Party never surrendered. Of course they still hold influence."

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "*Heavy* artillery fire you say? Tha..."
fields.Dialogue Text: *Heavy* artillery fire you say? That's the best kind of artillery fire. Very interesting.

fields.Title: Untitled hub (02)
René Arnoux: ""Martinaise was used as one of the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Martinaise was used as one of the three footholds in Revachol during Operation Death Blow in '08. The other two are off in Stella Maris and the Delta." He points to the northeast.

fields.Title: You: ""Commies didn't drive Guillaume out..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Commies didn't drive Guillaume out. He left, when things got bad and left Frissel to take the hit."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Preposterous! Surely you don't mea..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Preposterous! Surely you don't mean it." He frowns. "I'm just sorry it had to be them. After eight years of fighting those commie hyenas, boiling cats for food and drinking my piss in the mountains..."

René Arnoux: ""Yes," he nods, inspecting you with..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes," he nods, inspecting you with some disdain. "The military-coordinated amphibious landing to take back Revachol."

fields.Title: You: ""Is that why everything is so bombe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Is that why everything is so bombed out?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Damn right, son. They laid the fir..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Damn right, son. They laid the fire of hell on this city before they stormed it. And it worked, too." There is a strange gleam in his eyes.

fields.Title: Empathy: "This *Royal* failure weighs heavily..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This *Royal* failure weighs heavily on him.

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "Thinking men have *opinions* on the..."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Yes," he replies with a reluctant..."

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Yes, dammit -- I know! They laid t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yes, dammit -- I know! They laid the fire of hell on this city before they stormed it. And it worked, too." There is a strange gleam in his eyes.

fields.Title: Logic: "Exiled? Joyce said Guillaume ran an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Exiled? Joyce said Guillaume ran and his nephew, Frissel, was shot in his place.

fields.Dialogue Text: "This here is blood ground, where Coalition boots first made landfall and cleaned those rabid dogs out. Most likely," he says, looking down at the soil, "we're playing pétanque on their mangled corpses."

fields.Title: You: ""Foreign powers cleaned up our mess..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Foreign powers cleaned up our mess and now they rule us." (Shake your head in shame.)

fields.Dialogue Text: "They're *not*. And I'm sorry it had to be them. After eight years of fighting those hyenas, boiling cats for food and drinking piss in the mountains..." He takes a deep breath.

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Because this place is the damn Bea..."

fields.Title: Half Light: "He approves of this radical approac..."

fields.Title: You: ""That's how it should be. Soft soci..."

fields.Dialogue Text: "The Suzerain is the King. Has everyone forgotten already?" He then slowly nods and says to himself: "They've forgotten already."

Endurance: "That's our guy! The way he speaks a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's our guy! The way he speaks about the war and the bygone days -- Kingsman through and through -- ask him how to turn back time!

fields.Title: You: ""Do you know what created it?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Do you know what created it?"

fields.Title: You: ""Why was heavy artillery used?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why was heavy artillery used?"

fields.Title: René Arnoux: ""Instead, all that is just, holy, a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Instead, all that is just, holy, and beautiful in the world was wiped away and now it's neon signs with toothpaste ads everywhere. Foreign influence peddling garbage and stupid music on the radio." He sighs.
